In an age in which names like Al Qaeda and the Taliban have become the watchwords of global terrorism, it may seem a little passé to remember that Maoism was once a global scare word too.

Most of the world has forgotten, it seems, that Mao Zedong as the leader of China spread an ideology that inspired some of the world's most horrifying revolutions. The Khmer Rouge, led by Pol Pot, invoked Maoism
